summary:
The Security Council,
 Recalling previous resolutions on the Arab-Israeli conflict,
 Deeply concerned by tragic events since 28 September 2000, with numerous Palestinian deaths and injuries,
 Reaffirming the need for a just and lasting solution based on resolutions 242 (1967) and 338 (1973),
 Expressing support for the Middle East peace process,

1. Deplores the provocation at Al-Haram Al-Sharif in Jerusalem on 28 September 2000 and subsequent violence;
2. Condemns acts of violence, especially excessive use of force against Palestinians;
3. Calls upon Israel to abide by its obligations under the Fourth Geneva Convention;
4. Calls for immediate cessation of violence and new provocative actions;
5. Stresses the importance of establishing a mechanism for inquiry into recent events;
6. Calls for resumption of negotiations within the Middle East peace process;
7. Invites the Secretary-General to follow the situation and keep the Council informed;
8. Decides to follow closely the situation and remain seized of the matter.
